> Is anyone collecting the state quarters? I'd be happy to trade and watch
> for those others are having trouble finding. PA mint are easy to find here.
> Denver mint more difficult.

Me! Me!! And I'm missing all of the 2003 quarters at this point. Would
you believe that we have an American bank on post (Community Bank, run by
Bank of America) but they never get the new quarters? I've been only trying
to just get one of each, forget trying to find the different mints.

And as far as money goes, I've offered this before, but if you're interested
in Euros, I will bring some to trade away. If you have a complete set in
mind (1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 50 cent, 1 and 2 euro; worth about $4), email me in
advance of July 15 (I leave for America then) so I bring you a set. I also
have a pretty good sized bag of cool but worthless European money - USSR,
East German, Yugoslavian, etc. - that my son was given by a coin dealer.
He's sorted out what he wants, so the rest is up for grabs. Look for me in
SC if you're interested.

brenda

messages.messageBody:
WooHoo! I'm 9 digest behind but I just can't let this go by without
comment. I just can't wait to meet and see you all. TOMORROW is June 1st!
I don't even have to worry about my car braking down like I did last
year. We just bought a 2003 Ford Escape. I haven't had a new car in 25 yrs.
I'm so.. phyched!
Is anyone collecting the state quarters? I'd be happy to trade and watch
for those others are having trouble finding. PA mint are easy to find here.
Denver mint more difficult.

Barb E
The hardest battle is to be nobody but yourself

to make you like everybody else.

E.E. Cummings
